<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AIR-TO-AIR CHARGE AIR COOLER - CHARGE AIR COOLER HOSES AND
        CLAMPS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CHARGE AIR COOLER HOSES AND CLAMPS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>HOSES AND CLAMPS FOR EXHAUST (HOT) SIDE</title>
            <para>The correct material for the exhaust hose is silicone. It is a color other than black, frequently red
                or blue. Some silicone hoses have two humps with three wire reinforcements in the center (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200612">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200612" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200612" filename="../figg12/G1200612.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Silicone (Hump) Hose</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HUMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WIRE REINFORCEMENT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Always use a spring-loaded, T-bolt style hose clamp (
                <hotlnk document="s12006_10.xml" xrefid="f1200609">Figure 9</hotlnk>) to hold the silicone hose in place
                at the ends of the pipes to be joined. Place the clamp around the hose over the pipe end at each side of
                the joint, snug to the beaded end (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200613">Figure 13</hotlnk>). Tighten the clamp to the value found in the
                <hotlnk document="s12006_18.xml" xrefid="hl1200606">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1200606"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200613" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200613" filename="../figg12/G1200613.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Hose Clamp Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PIPE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CLAMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HOSE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
